text.section:
There is a State Insurance Program for providing and administering purchased insurance and self-insurance for the State, including:
insurance on State property;
insurance that federal law requires;
insurance trust agreements; and
insurance against other risk or commitment of the State.

section.section:
The Fund consists of:
each General Fund and special fund appropriation in the State budget to the Treasurer or a unit of the State government for self-insurance;
each General Fund and special fund appropriation to the State Insurance Trust Fund for payment under Title 12, Subtitle 5 of the State Government Article;
each premium that a unit of the State government pays for protection under the Fund;
each payment for a loss under purchased insurance; and
each payment from salvage or other recovery that results from a loss paid through the Program.
